= 1985

The mid-1980s present an unstable time for Soviet Communism. After 3 different leaders in the span of a few years in the early 1980s (Brezhnev,  Andropov, Chernenko), Gorbachev’s rise to power of the Soviet Union presents an opportunity for economic and political reform, and a revival of the Soviet Union’s power.

The task of Red Sunset  is to modernize Soviet Communism for the globalizing world, by playing as Mikhail Gorbachev, and keeping him in power. With increasing demands for prosperity, consumer goods, relations with the West, and more, it is YOUR job to keep Soviet Communism alive.

